 First, let's have a look at both expressions:
\begin{aligned}
&\quad\, (3p^3 - 5p + 6) \\
+&(4 - 6p^2 + 2p) \\
\end{aligned}
Now, let's combine like terms:
\begin{aligned} &= 3p^3-6p^2+2p-5p+6+4\\ \\ &= 3p^3-6p^2-3p+10\\ \\ &=(3)p^3+(-6)p^2+(-3)p+10\\ \end{aligned}
The question is asking for the answer expressed in that specific form
<answer> $3p^3-6p^2-3p+10$ </answer>

